{"key":"post-10832490","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10832490</id>\n<content>The shotgun terrarium as designed will be fine for FAE and humidity for the three days you're gone.&amp;nbsp; Don't even attempt to automate misting though.&amp;nbsp; That requires visually inspecting the substrates and then misting as required.&amp;nbsp; It's important that the substrate begins to dry out, and then you replace that moisture.&amp;nbsp; If it waterlogs or stays in a constant state, fruiting performance will be nil or poor.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you leave for three days, mist will before you leave, and if the substrates are dry when you return, soak them in water to rehydrate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10832654</next>\n<prev>10832238</prev>\n<first>10827734</first>\n<last>10832930</last>\n<when>1249924147</when>\n<utime>08/10/09 08:09 PM</utime>\n</post>"}